---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Title1 from "../components/mdx/typography/Title1.astro";
import Title2 from "../components/mdx/typography/Title2.astro";
import SmallCaps from "../components/mdx/typography/SmallCaps.astro";
import UnderlineHoverLink from "../components/mdx/UnderlineHoverLink.astro";
import PageWrapper from "../components/layouts/PageWrapper.astro";
// Image imports will be added when Karl provides photos
---

<!-- Photo randomization script will be added when photos are available -->

<Layout title="About Karl August" desc="ML student interested in AI safety, music, design, and mathematics.">
	<PageWrapper>
		<div class="header-section">
			<SmallCaps>About</SmallCaps>
			<Title1>Karl August Krogh Nybo</Title1>
			<Title2>ML student interested in AI safety, music, design, and mathematics.</Title2>
		</div>
		<div class="styled-main">
			<section class="intro">
				<div>
					<SmallCaps>A Little Context</SmallCaps>
					<p>
						I sit at the intersection of machine learning, AI safety, and creative expression. These three are
						at the core of everything I explore. I'm fascinated by how we can build safer AI systems while
						nurturing our creative instincts through music, film, and design.
					</p>
					<p>
						As an ML student, I'm particularly drawn to AI safety research and the ethical implications of
						artificial intelligence. But I don't just think about algorithms - I express myself through music
						production, occasional short filmmaking, and design experimentation.
					</p>
					<p>
						Here's what I'm currently exploring:
					</p>
					<div class="timeline">
						<div class="timeline-item">
							<div class="timeline-marker"></div>
							<div class="timeline-content">
								<div class="timeline-role-company">
									ML Student & AI Safety Researcher
								</div>
								<div class="timeline-year">2023 - Present</div>
								<div class="timeline-description">
									Studying machine learning with a focus on AI safety research. Exploring how we can
									build more robust and aligned AI systems that benefit humanity.
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="timeline-item">
							<div class="timeline-marker"></div>
							<div class="timeline-content">
								<div class="timeline-role-company">
									Music Producer & Sound Designer
								</div>
								<div class="timeline-year">2020 - Present</div>
								<div class="timeline-description">
									Creating experimental electronic music and soundscapes. Occasionally producing
									short films that blend visual storytelling with original compositions.
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="timeline-item">
							<div class="timeline-marker"></div>
							<div class="timeline-content">
								<div class="timeline-role-company">
									Design Enthusiast & Creative Coder
								</div>
								<div class="timeline-year">2019 - Present</div>
								<div class="timeline-description">
									Exploring the intersection of design and technology through creative coding projects.
									Love fiddling with interactive visualizations and generative art.
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="timeline-item">
							<div class="timeline-marker"></div>
							<div class="timeline-content">
								<div class="timeline-role-company">
									Mathematics Explorer
								</div>
								<div class="timeline-year">2018 - Present</div>
								<div class="timeline-description">
									Dabbling in mathematical concepts and their applications to machine learning and
									computational creativity. Always seeking elegant solutions to complex problems.
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p>
						This digital garden serves as my space to explore ideas at the intersection of technology,
						creativity, and ethics. I'm particularly interested in{" "}
						<UnderlineHoverLink href="/essays">AI alignment</UnderlineHoverLink>,{" "}
						<UnderlineHoverLink href="/garden-history">digital gardening</UnderlineHoverLink> as a
						method for knowledge cultivation, and{" "}
						<UnderlineHoverLink href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_creativity">
							computational creativity</UnderlineHoverLink>.
					</p>
					<SmallCaps>A Little History</SmallCaps>
					<p>
						I've always been fascinated by both the analytical and creative aspects of life. Growing up,
						I found equal joy in solving mathematical problems and creating music on my computer.
					</p>
					<p>
						This dual interest led me to explore machine learning, where I discovered the perfect blend
						of mathematical rigor and creative problem-solving. As I delved deeper into the field, I
						became increasingly concerned with the ethical implications of AI systems, which sparked my
						interest in AI safety research.
					</p>
					<p>
						Alongside my technical pursuits, I've continued to nurture my creative side through music
						production and occasional filmmaking. I believe that maintaining this creative outlet is
						essential for staying grounded and bringing fresh perspectives to technical challenges.
					</p>
					<p>
						Currently, I'm based in Copenhagen, balancing my studies in machine learning with creative
						projects and explorations in design and mathematics.
					</p>
				</div>
				{
					/* Placeholder for future photo of Karl August */
				}
			</section>
		</div>
	</PageWrapper>
</Layout>

<style>
	.header-section {
		margin: var(--space-m) auto 0;
	}
	.header-section :global(.small-caps) {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-3xs);
		color: var(--color-gray-600);
	}
	.header-section h1 {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-s);
	}
	.header-section h2 {
		color: var(--color-gray-800);
	}

	.styled-main {
		margin-top: var(--space-xs);
		padding: var(--space-xl) 0;
		width: 100%;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.styled-main {
			padding: var(--space-l) var(--space-xs);
		}
	}

	.styled-main img {
		border-radius: 4px;
	}

	.styled-main h2 {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-s);
	}

	.styled-main p {
		line-height: var(--leading-loose);
		max-width: 52ch;
	}

	.styled-main p:not(:last-of-type) {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-s);
	}

	.intro {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 4fr 3fr;
		gap: var(--space-xl);
		align-items: flex-start;
	}

	.intro :global(.small-caps):not(:first-of-type) {
		margin-top: var(--space-xl);
		color: var(--color-gray-900);
	}

	.intro :global(.small-caps)::before {
		content: "";
		display: inline-block;
		width: 20px;
		clear: both;
		height: 20px;
		margin-right: -1.5rem;
		background-image: url("/images/leaf-icon.svg");
		background-size: contain;
		background-repeat: no-repeat;
		position: relative;
		top: 4px;
		right: 2.25rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.intro {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: var(--space-m);
			flex-direction: column;
		}
	}

	.intro :global(.small-caps) {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	/* Timeline Styles */
	.timeline {
		position: relative;
		max-width: 64ch;
		margin: var(--space-l) 0 var(--space-xl) 0;
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
	}

	/* Timeline line */
	.timeline::before {
		content: "";
		position: absolute;
		left: 8px;
		top: 18px;
		bottom: -90px;
		width: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-gray-300) 75%, var(--color-cream) 90%);
	}

	.timeline-item {
		position: relative;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-l);
		padding-left: 2.5rem;
	}

	.timeline-item:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.timeline-marker {
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		top: 12px;
		width: 16px;
		height: 16px;
		background: var(--color-cream);
		border: 2px solid var(--color-gray-400);
		border-radius: 50%;
		z-index: 1;
	}

	.timeline-year {
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--color-gray-600);
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.025em;
	}

	.timeline-role-company {
		font-family: var(--font-body);
		font-size: var(--font-size-base);
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--color-gray-900);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-2xs);
		line-height: var(--leading-normal);
	}

	.timeline-description {
		color: var(--color-gray-700);
		line-height: var(--leading-base);
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.timeline {
			margin-left: var(--space-2xs);
		}

		.timeline::before {
			top: 15px;
			bottom: calc(var(--space-l) + 15px);
		}

		.timeline-item {
			padding-left: var(--space-l);
		}

		.timeline-marker {
			width: 20px;
			height: 20px;
			top: 10px;
		}
	}
</style>
